<TEXT>
the wife of an american convicted of spying for 
israel says she is sick and destitute and accused the israeli 
government of abandoning her 
jonathan pollard a former us navy analyst was sentenced to 
life in prison in 1987 for supplying classified us documents to 
israel his wife anne henderson pollard was sentenced to two 
concurrent fiveyear terms for helping him she was released six 
weeks ago 
i mean my god i gave up 40 months of my life to go to prison 
over this the israeli government did absolutely nothing for 
me mrs pollard 29 said in an interview friday with israel 
radio from the united states the report did not give her exact 
location 
mrs pollard denied published reports she and her husband 
received a monthly stipend of 5000 from israel 
if that was true why am i sitting here in destitution unable 
to even afford a residence a closet i have no money there is 
no money forthcoming she said 
foreign ministry spokesman yossi amihud refused to comment on 
mrs pollards accusations 
israeli officials have denied reports about the monthly stipend 
but a spokesman for prime minister yitzhak shamir said last year 
the government was working to have the couple freed on humanitarian 
grounds 
mrs pollard said she had not visited her husband since her 
release becaus she is too ill and too broke to travel jonathan 
pollard 35 is in a federal prison in marion ill 
mrs pollard who complained of stomach pain throughout her 
prison stay said she also suffers from nerve eye and skin 
disorders 
