<TEXT>
military helicopters rushed food and 
water today to tens of thousands of people who were left marooned 
by a cyclone that killed at least 299 of their countrymen 
news reports said an estimated 90000 farm animals died in 
indias worst storm in a decade reducing already sparse food 
supplies in many areas 
press trust of india said 20 navy and air force helicopters 
dropped 15400 pounds of food medicine and water to tens of 
thousands of people stranded in the lowlying coastal plain of 
andhra pradesh state 
rainy weather prevented helicopters from reaching thousands of 
other people who passed a third day without food and water 
the navy sent 50 boats to a small peninsula jutting into the bay 
of bengal to evacuate thousands of people 
officials gave new damage estimates today from the storm which 
struck the southern coastal states of andhra pradesh and tamil nadu 
on wednesday with winds up to 155 mph tidal waves struck the area 
ahead of the storm on tuesday 
officials said 300 million of crops had been destroyed 
including 435000 acres of rice paddies huge tracts of mangos and 
bananas were also lost 
flood waters continued to rise in some areas 
prime minister vp singh visited the coastal town of annavarm 
where a reservoir flooded forcing many residents to seek shelter 
in a nearby temple 
singh said the government would spend at least 52 million to 
provide relief for those affected by the storm but he also 
appealed to the public for clothes medicine and food to help 
victims of the cyclone 
