a helicopter clements office said 
hes done everything he can from austin said clements 
press secretary rossanna salazar and out of concern for the 
situation he wanted to see it firsthand 
the trinity river authority which normally releases less than 
15000 cubic feet per second of water at lake livingston on friday 
released 39300 cubic feet per second it warned of record releases 
as high as 85000 cubic feet for five days next week 
maj jack sherer of the us army corps of engineers warned that 
banks along the red river are soft from so much water and pose a 
threat 
you could easily slide right into the river and theres not 
much chance of surviving he said 
