getting his election campaign geared up 
other theories abound among democrats 
some think republicans want to trap democrats into backing an 
electionyear tax increase others think bush was frightened by the 
recent passage by the senate budget committee and the full house of 
democraticwritten budgets that slashed the presidents defense 
program 
whats clear is if bush and congress do not agree to reduce the 
deficit the grammrudman law will do it automatically 
without a budget deal the law will slash defense and domestic 
spending on oct 1 the start of fiscal 1991 by whatever amount 
is needed to shrink the deficit to 64 billion most in washington 
agree that such cuts would be unbearable for the millions of 
americans who rely on the government for aid and for business 
the president thinks this is a good opportunity to get going 
that times a wasting said rep bill frenzel of minnesota 
ranking republican on the house budget committee we dont have a 
lot of time to work this out 
