speech friday night carried live by several local television and 
radio stations 
new yorks first black mayor said the nations largest city has 
many problems including expensive housing crack and aids 
epidemics and a faltering economy 
unfortunately some smallminded people prey upon these 
pressures spreading a message not of unity but of division i 
challenge all of the people of this city to reject these calls to 
bigotry he said 
all of us want to live our lives in peace and dignity free 
to walk any street and shop in any store at any time in any 
neighborhood without fear of force or violence 
a few hours before he spoke scores of demonstrators jostled a 
