real estate taxes from about 400 to 1200 
we hear all the time from people you got a new house you 
ought to be happy and satisfied you should just shut up 
renfrow said the general public doesnt know what were going 
through 
what outsiders also fail to understand renfrow said is that 
osage residents problems didnt start with the fire they have 
been under duress since before 1982 when they first met with city 
officials to complain about the garbage and excrement surrounding 
the move house and about the nightly barrage of insults and even 
death threats the move members broadcast through bullhorns 
move whose initials dont stand for anything began in the 70s 
protesting peacefully against abuse of animals the elderly and the 
environment its surviving members say but followers became more 
militant and began having scrapes with the law and in 1978 a 
police officer was slain while attempting to evict move from a 
house 
in the osage avenue confrontation the city tried negotiation 
before force 
may 13 began with a demand from police to evacuate the move 
house a barrage of bullets followed firefighters tried 
unsuccessfully to clear a fortified bunker on the roof with water 
canons the bitterly disputed decision was made to drop a bomb 
we asked that they be evicted we did not ask for them to be 
killed said renfrow 
a county grand jury was convened and brought no charges against 
mayor w wilson goode but found him grossly negligent in 
handling the situation 
the mayor has said less each year about the move disaster and 
this year declined to be interviewed by the associated press 
im still very much troubled by what happened goode told 
the philadelphia inquirer in an interview in sundays editions i 
continue to grieve for those who lost their lives and those who 
lost their homes 
