italianmade parts were for the rear portion of a giant artillery 
piece they said the weapon would be capable of firing projectiles 
hundreds of miles including nuclear or chemical warheads 
documents seized friday along with the components indicate that 
the parts were for oil field equipment ordered by iraqs ministry 
of industry 
italian law prohibits the sale or shipment of arms to iraq 
on april 12 british customs officer seized eight giant tubes 
earmarked for shipment to iraq military experts said they could be 
used as the barrel of a giant gun 
british customs officers have said the tubes built could be 
assembled to make a 131footlong gun barrel with a 39inch bore 
iraq has said the parts were for a petrochemical project and 
denied it is building a super gun 
on april 20 greek authorities confiscated some 30 tons of metal 
tubing believed to be another component of the gun italian police 
said saturday that the metal tubing seized in greece had been 
shipped earlier through the port of brindisi in italy 
