is slumping in the ratings alternating with the cbs evening 
news in third place 
friedman helped today become first in the ratings before he 
left nbc in 1987 
the new york times quoted one unidentified nbc executive as 
saying the appointment signaled that former today cohost jane 
pauley would soon become coanchor of the newscast with brokaw the 
executive predicted ms pauleys addition to the broadcast would be 
gradual with no definitive move until the fall saturdays times 
reported 
